        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 21 at 12:28AM EDT until July 21 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values up to 106 expected.

* WHERE...Chatham, Durham, Orange, and Wake Counties.

* WHEN...From 11 AM this morning to 8 PM EDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Multiple days of dangerous heat and minimal
overnight relief will compound to make heat related illnesses more
likely.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check on relatives and neighbors.

Take extra precautions when outside. Wear lightweight and loose
fitting clothing. Try to limit strenuous activities to early morning
or evening. Take action when you see symptoms of heat exhaustion or
heat stroke.</instruction>
